    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "The credibility assessment team determined that the overall evidence package supports a Medium assurance level for the non-cannulated pedicle screw FEA model under ASTM F1717 compression-bending. Twelve of thirteen V&V 40 factors meet or exceed their required gradation levels. The single shortfall in Test conditions (achieved Gradation 2 vs. required Gradation 3) was reviewed and judged not to materially affect the regulatory decision, as the primary QoI acceptance criteria are met across all 11 constructs and the submission scope is limited to the single standard F1717 configuration. Medium assurance is declared consistent with Model Risk Level 3 and the available evidence.",
